{
  "title": [
    "velvet~"
  ],
  "description": "velvet noise generator",
  "origin": "ELSE",
  "categories": [
    "Signal Generators"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "frequency in Hz"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "polarity bias (0-1)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "time regularity (0-1)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "float/signal",
          "description": "amplitude irregularity (0-1)"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "velvet noise signal"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "frequency in Hz",
      "default": "0"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "polarity bias",
      "default": "0.5"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "time regularity",
      "default": "0"
    },
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "amplitude irregularity",
      "default": "0"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [
    {
      "name": "-seed <float>",
      "description": "sets random seed\ndefault: unique internal"
    },
    {
      "name": "-ch <float>",
      "description": "sets number of channels\ndefault: 1"
    }
  ],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "seed <float>",
      "description": "a float sets seed, no float sets a unique internal"
    }
  ],
  "body": "[velvet~] is a velvet noise generator, which randomly chooses either positive (1) or negative (-1) impulses at random positions in a given period set in Hz. A polarity bias is possible to set the amount of positive and negative impulses. A time regularity parameter forces a impulses with less randomness. An amplitude irregularity forces random values (different than 1 or -1). The object has support for multichannel."
}